                        <data>linecounter.bat </data>

                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>@echo off
set TEST=NOTFOUND
if NOT exist %1 goto END
for /f &quot;tokens=*&quot; %%a in (
 &apos;find /c /v &quot;~`!@#$^&amp;*()_+&quot; %1&apos;
) do for %%b in (%%a) do set TEST=%%b
:END
echo filename,linecount
echo %1,%TEST%
</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>linecounter.bat</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>

        <sampler name="Generate HSBC msg tracker orders">
            <sampleInterval>
                <data>0</data>
            </sampleInterval>
            <sampleOnStartup>false</sampleOnStartup>
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>../Rogers_Perl_script.pl |tee Martins_INPUT &gt; Martins_OUTPUT</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>#!/usr/bin/perl -w

while ( 1 ) {

my $count = 0;
while ($count &lt;= 2500) {


        my $id = int( rand(1000000000) );

        my $timeStart = time;

        my $strStartMS = &quot;99999&quot; . sprintf( &quot;%01d&quot;, int( rand(10) ) );
        my $strStart = $timeStart . &quot;.&quot; . $strStartMS;

        my $strEndMS = sprintf( &quot;%06d&quot;, int( rand(1000000) /30000 ) );
        my $strEnd = $timeStart+1 . &quot;.&quot; . $strEndMS;

        print &quot;,&quot; . $strStart . &quot;,G,xxx,$id&quot; . &quot;\n&quot;;

        print &quot;,&quot; . $strEnd . &quot;,E,xxx,$id&quot; . &quot;\n&quot;;

        $count++
}

        sleep (1)

}</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>../Rogers_Perl_script.pl</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
            <dataviews>
                <dataview name="">
                    <additions>
                        <var-headlines>
                            <data>
                                <headline>
                                    <data></data>
                                </headline>
                            </data>
                        </var-headlines>
                    </additions>
                </dataview>
            </dataviews>

        <sampler name="New Sampler 13">
            <var-hideColumns>
                <data>
                    <column>
                        <data>Power Management</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Delete Task If Not Rescheduled</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Schedule</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Repeat</data>
                    </column>
                </data>
            </var-hideColumns>
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>c:\Windows\System32\cscript.exe /nologo taskscript.vbs</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>function extractFieldValue(line)
s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
str = Replace(s(1), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
extractFieldValue = trim(str)
end function
 
function extractFieldName(line)
s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
str = Replace(s(0), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
extractFieldName = trim(str)
end function
 
jobfilter = &quot;&quot; 
 
&apos;***** Run the command
 
Set WshShell = WScript.CreateObject(&quot;WScript.Shell&quot;)
Set oExec = WshShell.Exec(&quot;c:\windows\system32\schtasks.exe /query /fo list /v&quot;)
 
newline = &quot;&quot;
header = &quot;&quot;
first = 1
 
&apos;***** Process the output
Do While oExec.StdOut.AtEndOfStream &lt;&gt; True
 
sline=oExec.StdOut.ReadLine
 
 
if sline = &quot;&quot; then 
&apos;****This is the line break
if newline &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then
 
if first = 1 and header &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then
&apos;**** Print column headers
 
header = left(header,len(header)-1)
wscript.echo header
header = &quot;&quot;
first = 0
end if
 
&apos;***Remove last comma
newline = left(newline,len(newline)-1)
 
if(InStr(newline,jobfilter) &gt; 0) then
wscript.echo newline
end if
 
newline = &quot;&quot;
 
 
end if
 
elseif (InStr(1, sline,&quot;Folder:&quot;) &gt; 0) or (InStr(1, sline,&quot;INFO:&quot;) &gt; 0) then
 
&apos;wscript.echo &quot;folder&quot;
 
else
 
newline = newline &amp; extractFieldValue(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;
 
if first = 1 then
header = header &amp; extractFieldName(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;
&apos;wscript.echo header
end if
 
&apos;wscript.echo extractFieldValue(sline)
 
end if
 
Loop</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>taskscript.vbs</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
            <dataviews>
                <dataview name="Scheduled Tasks">
                    <firstColumn>
                        <create>
                            <columnName>Long Task Name</columnName>
                            <combineColumns>
                                <column>HostName</column>
                                <literal> </literal>
                                <column>TaskName</column>
                            </combineColumns>
                        </create>
                    </firstColumn>
                </dataview>

                                    <data>service:jmx:rmi:///jndi/rmi://</data>

        <sampler name="put EDUs webslinger wget script">
            <sampleInterval>
                <data>0</data>
            </sampleInterval>
            <sampleOnStartup>true</sampleOnStartup>
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>EDUemail.pl</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>#!/usr/bin/perl

#---------------------------------------------
# Written by Edu A. Morales ITRS AMERICA INC. &amp;copy 2008-2009
#_____________________________________________

use strict;
use warnings;
my $ESCALATE = $0 =~ /escalate/ ? &apos;E&apos; : &apos;&apos;;

#---------------------------------------------
my $FROM = &quot;itrsMonitoringNY\@itrsgroup.com&quot;;
my $OutputFile=&quot;/tmp/Mail$$.html&quot;;

#example Date: Fri, 15 Aug 2008 15:45:20 -0400 (EDT)
my $DateString = `date +&quot;%a, %d %b %Y %H:%M:%S %z&quot;`;
chomp ($DateString);
#_____________________________________________

#---------------------------------------------
# set recipients
my ($EMAIL,$InfoMessage,$Comment,$SUBJECT);
# if this is defined then it is a user assignment email
if (defined $ENV{&apos;_ASSIGNEE_EMAIL&apos;} ) {
    $EMAIL = $ENV{&apos;_ASSIGNEE_EMAIL&apos;};
    my $assign = lc shift;
    $InfoMessage = &quot;You have been $assign this task by $ENV{&apos;_ASSIGNER_USERNAME&apos;}.&lt;br&gt;\n&quot;;
    $Comment = $ENV{&apos;_COMMENT&apos;};
}
# standard alert email
else {
    $EMAIL = $ENV{&apos;eMail&apos;};
    $InfoMessage = &quot;This Message has been generated by the ITRS monitoring application.&lt;br&gt;
For more information on problem resolutions, escalation procedures and contact numbers please visit the support homepage.&lt;br&gt;\n&quot;;
    $Comment = $ENV{&apos;_USERDATA&apos;};
}
#_____________________________________________


#--------------------------------------------------
### Create a smart subject
my $SUBJECT;
# create severity substring used in subject 
my $SEV = $ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;} eq &apos;OK&apos; ? &apos;OK&apos; : $ESCALATE . substr($ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;},0,1); 
#

$SUBJECT = sprintf &quot;(%2s) %s %s&quot;, $SEV, $ENV{&apos;Environment&apos;},
    defined $ENV{&apos;_SUBJECT&apos;} ? $ENV{&apos;_SUBJECT&apos;} : &quot;$ENV{&apos;_HOSTNAME&apos;} $ENV{&apos;_VARIABLE&apos;} &quot;;

#---------------------------------------------
open (OUT, &quot;&gt; $OutputFile&quot; ) or die &quot;Cannot open $OutputFile: $!\n&quot;;

# moved all of the html to subroutines so that it is easier to read
# Standard HTML email header
&amp;printHeader;
print OUT $InfoMessage;

# start the html table
&amp;printStartTable;
&amp;printRow(&apos;Managed Entity&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_MANAGED_ENTITY&apos;});
&amp;printRow(&apos;Box&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_HOSTNAME&apos;});
&amp;printRow(&apos;Host&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_NETPROBE_HOST&apos;});

&amp;printBlankLine;

my $COLOR =
    $ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;} =~ /CRITICAL/i ? &apos;#D42A2A&apos; :
    $ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;} =~ /WARNING/i ? &apos;#D4D400&apos; :
    $ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;} =~ /OK/i ? &apos;#55AA2A&apos; :
    &apos;darkgrey&apos;;

&amp;printRowColor ($COLOR,&apos;Severity&apos;,&quot;$ENV{&apos;_SEVERITY&apos;}&quot;);

&amp;printBlankLine;

&amp;printRow(&apos;Variable&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_VARIABLE&apos;});
&amp;printRow(&apos;Value&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_VALUE&apos;});
&amp;printRow(&apos;Comments&apos;,$ENV{&apos;_USERDATA&apos;});
&amp;printEndTable;
#_____________________________________________

#---------------------------------------------
# print out footer
print OUT &quot;&lt;br&gt;\n&quot;;
print OUT &quot;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;/BODY&gt;\n&quot;;
close (OUT);

`/usr/lib/sendmail -i -t -O ErrorMode=q &lt; $OutputFile`;

unlink $OutputFile;

exit;
# end of main script
#_____________________________________________

#---------------------------------------------
# subroutines

# format the header of the html e-mail
sub printHeader {
    print OUT &quot;To: $EMAIL\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;Subject:$SUBJECT\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;Date: $DateString\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;X-MS-Has-Attach:\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;X-MS-TNEF-Correlator:\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;MIME-Version: 1.0\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;X-Priority: 1 (Highest)\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;Content-Type: text/html; charset=us-ascii\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;Content-Disposition: inline; filename=CreateHTML.mail\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;From:$FROM\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;&lt;TEXTFORMAT LEADING=2&gt;&lt;P ALIGN=LEFT&gt;&lt;FONT FACE=Arial SIZE=2 COLOR=black LETTERSPACING=0 KERNING=0&gt;\n&quot;;
}

# start an HTML table
sub printStartTable {
    print OUT &quot;&lt;TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1 BGCOLOR=\&quot;SILVER\&quot;&gt;\n&quot;;
    return;
}

# end an HTML table
sub printEndTable {
    print OUT &quot;&lt;/TABLE&gt;\n&quot;;
    return;
}

# print a 2 column row, (name,value)
sub printRow {
    my $CellName  = shift;
    my $CellValue = shift;
    $CellValue = &quot;&amp;nbsp;&quot; if (!defined $CellValue);

    print OUT &quot;&lt;TR&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;  &lt;TD&gt;&lt;b&gt;$CellName&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/TD&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;  &lt;TD&gt;$CellValue&lt;/TD&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;&lt;/TR&gt;\n&quot;;
    return;
}

# print a 2 column row with the value in color (color,name,value)
sub printRowColor {
    my $COLOR     = shift;
    my $CellName  = shift;
    my $CellValue = shift;
    $CellValue = &quot;&amp;nbsp;&quot; if (!defined $CellValue);

    print OUT &quot;&lt;TR&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;  &lt;TD&gt;&lt;b&gt;$CellName&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/TD&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;  &lt;TD bgcolor=\&quot;$COLOR\&quot;&gt;$CellValue&lt;/TD&gt;\n&quot;;
    print OUT &quot;&lt;/TR&gt;\n&quot;;
    return;
}

# prints a blank line in a tbale that spans 2 columns
sub printBlankLine {
    print OUT &quot;&lt;tr bgcolor=\&quot;white\&quot;&gt;&lt;td colspan=\&quot;2\&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\n&quot;;
    return;
}
</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>EDUemail.pl</data>
                        </filename>

        <sampler name="Scheduled Tasks">
            <var-hideColumns>
                <data>
                    <column>
                        <data>Power Management</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Delete Task If Not Rescheduled</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Schedule</data>
                    </column>
                    <column>
                        <data>Repeat</data>
                    </column>
                </data>
            </var-hideColumns>
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>c:\Windows\System32\cscript.exe /nologo taskscript.vbs</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>function extractFieldValue(line)
s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
str = Replace(s(1), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
extractFieldValue = trim(str)
end function
 
function extractFieldName(line)
s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
str = Replace(s(0), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
extractFieldName = trim(str)
end function
 
jobfilter = &quot;&quot; 
 
&apos;***** Run the command
 
Set WshShell = WScript.CreateObject(&quot;WScript.Shell&quot;)
Set oExec = WshShell.Exec(&quot;c:\windows\system32\schtasks.exe /query /fo list /v&quot;)
 
newline = &quot;&quot;
header = &quot;&quot;
first = 1
 
&apos;***** Process the output
Do While oExec.StdOut.AtEndOfStream &lt;&gt; True
 
sline=oExec.StdOut.ReadLine
 
 
if sline = &quot;&quot; then 
&apos;****This is the line break
if newline &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then
 
if first = 1 and header &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then
&apos;**** Print column headers
 
header = left(header,len(header)-1)
wscript.echo header
header = &quot;&quot;
first = 0
end if
 
&apos;***Remove last comma
newline = left(newline,len(newline)-1)
 
if(InStr(newline,jobfilter) &gt; 0) then
wscript.echo newline
end if
 
newline = &quot;&quot;
 
 
end if
 
elseif (InStr(1, sline,&quot;Folder:&quot;) &gt; 0) or (InStr(1, sline,&quot;INFO:&quot;) &gt; 0) then
 
&apos;wscript.echo &quot;folder&quot;
 
else
 
newline = newline &amp; extractFieldValue(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;
 
if first = 1 then
header = header &amp; extractFieldName(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;
&apos;wscript.echo header
end if
 
&apos;wscript.echo extractFieldValue(sline)
 
end if
 
Loop</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>taskscript.vbs</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
            <dataviews>
                <dataview name="Scheduled Tasks">
                    <firstColumn>
                        <create>
                            <columnName>Long Task Name</columnName>
                            <combineColumns>
                                <column>HostName</column>
                                <literal> </literal>

        <sampler name="Scheduled Tasks_vbs">
            <sampleInterval>

            </sampleInterval>
            <var-hideColumns>

            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>c:\Windows\System32\cscript.exe /nologo taskscript.vbs</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>function extractFieldValue(line)
  s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
  str = Replace(s(1), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
  extractFieldValue = trim(str)
end function

function extractFieldName(line)
  s = split(line,&quot;:&quot;,2)
  str = Replace(s(0), &quot;,&quot;, &quot;;&quot;)
  extractFieldName = trim(str)
end function

jobfilter = &quot;ITRS&quot;


&apos;***** Run the command

Set WshShell = WScript.CreateObject(&quot;WScript.Shell&quot;)
Set oExec = WshShell.Exec(&quot;c:\windows\system32\schtasks.exe /query /fo list /v&quot;)

newline = &quot;&quot;
header  = &quot;&quot;
first = 1

&apos;***** Process the output
Do While oExec.StdOut.AtEndOfStream &lt;&gt; True

  sline=oExec.StdOut.ReadLine


  if sline = &quot;&quot; then
    &apos;****This is the line break
    if newline &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then

      if first = 1 and header &lt;&gt; &quot;&quot; then
    &apos;**** Print column headers

        header = left(header,len(header)-1)
        wscript.echo header
        header = &quot;&quot;
        first = 0
      end if

      &apos;***Remove last comma
      newline = left(newline,len(newline)-1)


      newline = &quot;&quot;


    end if

  elseif (InStr(1, sline,&quot;Folder:&quot;) &gt; 0) or (InStr(1, sline,&quot;INFO:&quot;) &gt; 0) then

    &apos;wscript.echo &quot;folder&quot;

  else

    newline = newline &amp; extractFieldValue(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;

    if first = 1 then
        header = header &amp; extractFieldName(sline) &amp; &quot;,&quot;
        &apos;wscript.echo header
    end if

    &apos;wscript.echo extractFieldValue(sline)

  end if

Loop</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>taskscript.vbs</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
            <dataviews>
                <dataview name="Scheduled Tasks">
                    <firstColumn>
                        <create>
                            <columnName>Long Task Name</columnName>
                            <combineColumns>
                                <column>HostName</column>
                                <literal> </literal>
                                <column>TaskName</column>
                            </combineColumns>
                        </create>
                    </firstColumn>
                </dataview>
            </dataviews>

        <sampler name="SNMPWALK">
            <plugin>
                <!--
        Make sure you have net-snmp installed on your netprobe host.
        Download all the MIBS. On Ubuntu this is done through a single package that then fetches all the MIBs into /usr/share/mibs/*:
        
        $ sudo apt-get install snmp-mibs-downloader
       
    The following works using the toolkits environment variables functionality.
    HOST=<ip address>
    COMMUNITY=<snmp community>
    VENDOR=<prefix for vendor mib files, e.g. CISCO>
    TABLE=<snmp table to be displayed>
    MIBDIR=<location of mibfiles>
    
    SNMP* and RFC* are almost always required by other mibfiles, but there may be more I did not account for.

    The number of MIB files that snmptable is loading in impacts runtime.  
    To improve performance I created a sub folder with only the files I needed, 
    and the corresponding dependencies, and altered the mibdirs to point to just that 
    (symlinked of course).
-->
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>SnmpWalk.sh</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <environmentVariables>
                        <variable>
                            <name>HOST</name>
                            <value>
                                <data>&lt;ip address&gt;</data>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                        <variable>
                            <name>COMMUNITY</name>
                            <value>
                                <data>&lt;snmp community string&gt;</data>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                        <variable>
                            <name>VENDOR</name>
                            <value>
                                <data>&lt;prefix for vendor mib files, e.g. CISCO&gt;</data>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                        <variable>
                            <name>TABLE</name>
                            <value>
                                <data>&lt;snmp table to be displayed&gt; </data>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                        <variable>
                            <name>MIBDIR</name>
                            <value>
                                <data>&lt;location of mibfiles&gt; </data>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                    </environmentVariables>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>#!/bin/bash
#Create colon separated list of mib files
MIBFILES=`find ${MIBDIR} -type f | egrep -i &quot;${MIBDIR}/(RFC|SNMP|$VENDOR)&quot; | tr &quot;\n&quot; &quot;:&quot;`
timeIN=`date &quot;+%s.%N&quot;`
snmptable ${HOST} -v2c -c ${COMMUNITY} -m ${MIBFILES} -Cf , -Ln ${TABLE} | sed -e &apos;s/\&quot;//g&apos; | sed -e &apos;1,/^$/d&apos;
timeOUT=`date &quot;+%s.%N&quot;`
# display snmp acq time like mibmon does
delta=`echo &quot;${timeOUT} - ${timeIN}&quot;|bc`
echo &quot;&lt;!&gt;acquisitionTime,${delta} secs&quot;</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>SnmpWalk.sh</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
        </sampler>
        <sampler name="snmpwalk to create dataviews from SNMP tables">
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>./snmptest.sh ipRouteTable localhost public</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>#!/bin/sh  
TABLE=$1 
HOST=$2 
COMMUNITY=$3  
snmptable $HOST -v2c -c $COMMUNITY -M /usr/share/mibs/ietf -m ALL -Cf , -Ln $TABLE| sed -e &apos;1,/^$/d&apos;</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>snmptest.sh</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
        </sampler>
        <sampler name="Snoozed Data History">
            <sampleInterval>
                <data>600</data>
            </sampleInterval>
            <plugin>
                <sql-toolkit>
                    <queries>
                        <query>
                            <name>
                                <data>Snoozed Data History</data>
                            </name>
                            <sql>
                                <data>SELECT CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      GATEWAY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 14),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      NETPROBE,
   managedentity MANAGED_ENTITY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      SAMPLER,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) + 15),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      CELL,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:un&apos;) = 0 THEN &apos;Snoozed&apos;
      ELSE &apos;Unsnoozed&apos;
   END
      ACTION,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description, instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:&apos;) + 8),
            &apos; &apos;,
            1)
   END
      TYPE,
   SUBSTRING(username, -7) SNOOZED_BY,
   FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp) TIME,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(description, instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) + 13)
   END
      USER_COMMENT,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(
            description,
            instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;),
            instr(substring(description, instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;)),
                  &apos;User comment:&apos;)
            - 1)
   END
      FULL_PATH_TO_TARGET
FROM audit_table
WHERE description LIKE &apos;%/SNOOZE:%&apos;
ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
</data>
                            </sql>
                        </query>
                        <query>
                            <name>
                                <data>One Day</data>
                            </name>
                            <sql>
                                <data>SELECT CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      GATEWAY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 14),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      NETPROBE,
   managedentity MANAGED_ENTITY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      SAMPLER,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) + 15),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      CELL,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:un&apos;) = 0 THEN &apos;Snoozed&apos;
      ELSE &apos;Unsnoozed&apos;
   END
      ACTION,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description, instr(description, &apos;/SNOOZE:&apos;) + 8),
            &apos; &apos;,
            1)
   END
      TYPE,
   SUBSTRING(username, -7) SNOOZED_BY,
   FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp) TIME,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(description, instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) + 13)
   END
      USER_COMMENT,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(
            description,
            instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;),
            instr(substring(description, instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;)),
                  &apos;User comment:&apos;)
            - 1)
   END
      FULL_PATH_TO_TARGET
FROM audit_table
WHERE description LIKE &apos;%/SNOOZE:%&apos;
ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
</data>
                            </sql>
                        </query>
                    </queries>

  WHERE managedEntity LIKE &apos;52051&apos;

  FROM audit_table 
  WHERE managedEntity LIKE &apos;52051&apos;

        <sampler name="UserAssignment History">
            <sampleInterval>
                <data>600</data>
            </sampleInterval>
            <plugin>
                <sql-toolkit>
                    <queries>
                        <query>
                            <name>
                                <data>User Assignment History</data>
                            </name>
                            <sql>
                                <data>
SELECT CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;gateway[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      GATEWAY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;probe[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 14),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      NETPROBE,
   managedentity MANAGED_ENTITY,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;sampler[(@name=&quot;&apos;) + 16),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      SAMPLER,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;cell[(@column=&quot;&apos;) + 15),
            &apos;&quot;)]&apos;,
            1)
   END
      CELL,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/USERASSIGNMENT:un&apos;) = 0 THEN &apos;Assignment&apos;
      ELSE &apos;Unassignment&apos;
   END
      ACTION,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;/USERASSIGNMENT:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring_index(
            substring(description,
                      instr(description, &apos;/USERASSIGNMENT:&apos;) + 16),
            &apos; &apos;,
            1)
   END
      TYPE,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;User:&apos;) = 0 THEN SUBSTRING(username, -7)
      ELSE substring(description, instr(description, &apos;User:&apos;) + 5, 7)
   END
      ASSIGNEE,
   SUBSTRING(username, -7) ASSIGNER,
   FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp) TIME,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(description, instr(description, &apos;User comment:&apos;) + 13)
   END
      USER_COMMENT,
   CASE
      WHEN instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;) = 0
      THEN
         &apos;&apos;
      ELSE
         substring(
            description,
            instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;),
            instr(substring(description, instr(description, &apos;DataItem&apos;)),
                  &apos;User comment:&apos;)
            - 1)
   END
      FULL_PATH_TO_TARGET
FROM audit_table
WHERE description LIKE &apos;%USERASSIGNMENT:%&apos;
ORDER BY timestamp DESC;</data>
                            </sql>
                        </query>
                    </queries>
                    <connection>
                        <database>
                            <mysql>
                                <var-serverName>
                                    <data>gbwxaphubd01.uk.ml.com</data>
                                </var-serverName>
                                <var-databaseName>
                                    <data>gmot_gatemon_emea_lo_uat</data>
                                </var-databaseName>
                                <var-port>
                                    <data>3306</data>
                                </var-port>

                        <var-userName>

                    <showRowLine>true</showRowLine>
                </sql-toolkit>

        <sampler name="Windows_PortMonitor">
            <var-group>
                <data>Port</data>
            </var-group>
            <plugin>
                <toolkit>
                    <samplerScript>
                        <data>C:\windows\Syswow64\cscript.exe /NoLogo ListenCount.vbs</data>
                    </samplerScript>
                    <environmentVariables>
                        <variable>
                            <name>LocalPortFilter</name>
                            <value>
                                <var ref="FilterList"></var>
                            </value>
                        </variable>
                    </environmentVariables>
                    <script>
                        <contents>
                            <data>Set WshShell = CreateObject(&quot;Wscript.Shell&quot;)

&apos;Let user set a local port to filter on that is set as an environment variable
&apos;This needs to be | seperated
LocalPortFilter=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(&quot;%LocalPortFilter%&quot;)

&apos;Init Variables
rowCount=0
Dim resultArray ()

&apos;Load in regex
Set regEx  = New RegExp
Set regExN = New RegExp

&apos;Regex pattern for Title Line
regExN.Pattern = &quot;Proto\s+(\S+\s\S+)\s+(\S+\s\S+)\s+(\S+)&quot;

&apos;Regex pattern for TCP line
&apos;Test to see if local port is set use corresponding Regex
if (LocalPortFilter &lt;&gt; &quot;%LocalPortFilter%&quot;) then
        regEx.Pattern = &quot;TCP\s+(\S+:(?:&quot; &amp; LocalPortFilter &amp; &quot;))\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)&quot;
        Dim filterArray
        filterArray = Split(LocalPortFilter,&quot;|&quot;)
Else
        regEx.Pattern = &quot;TCP\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)&quot;
End If


processNetStat
If (LocalPortFilter &lt;&gt; &quot;%LocalPortFilter%&quot;) then
        printFilter
Else
        printNoFilter
End If

&apos;&apos;SubRoutines
&apos;Print function without filter
Sub printNoFilter()
        For Each result in resultArray
                wscript.echo result
        Next
        wscript.echo &quot;&lt;!&gt;RowsMatched,&quot; &amp; rowCount
End Sub

&apos;Print function with filter and availability
Sub printFilter()
        wscript.echo resultArray(0)

        If UBound(resultArray) &gt; 0 Then
        For arrayIndex = 1 To UBound(resultArray)
                wscript.echo resultArray(arrayIndex)
        Next
        Else
                arrayIndex=1
        End If
        For Each port in filterArray
                matchArray=Filter(resultArray,&quot;:&quot; &amp; port &amp; &quot;,0.0.0.0:0,LISTENING&quot;,True,1)
                If UBound(matchArray) &lt; 0 Then
                        wscript.echo &quot;0.0.0.0:&quot;&amp;port&amp;&quot;-0.0.0.0:0&quot; &amp; &quot;,0.0.0.0:&quot; &amp; port &amp; &quot;,0.0.0.0:0,Absent&quot;
                        arrayIndex=arrayIndex+1
                End If
        Next
        wscript.echo &quot;&lt;!&gt;RowsMatched,&quot; &amp; rowCount
        wscript.echo &quot;&lt;!&gt;Filter,&quot; &amp; LocalPortFilter
End Sub

Sub processNetStat()
        &apos; netstat command to only list tcp connections
        set oExec = WshShell.Exec(&quot;netstat -anp tcp&quot;)
        
        &apos; loop through output
        Do While oExec.StdOut.AtEndOfStream &lt;&gt; True
                sLine=trim(oExec.StdOut.ReadLine)
                
                &apos;Header line
                If (InStr(1,sLine,&quot;Proto&quot;,1) &gt; 0) then
                        new_line = regExN.Replace(sLine, &quot;$1,$2,$3&quot;)
                        ReDim Preserve resultArray(0)
                        resultArray(0) = &quot;name,&quot; &amp; new_line
                        &apos;TCP line
                ElseIf (InStr(1,sLine,&quot;TCP&quot;,1) &gt; 0) then
                        Dim objMatches
                        Set objMatches = regEx.Execute(sLine)
                        &apos;If regex matches print out sub strings
                        If (objMatches.Count = 1) then
                                rowCount=rowCount+1
                                ReDim Preserve resultArray(rowCount)
                                &apos;resultArray(rowCount) = rowCount &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp; objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(0) &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp;objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(1) &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp; objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(2)
                                resultArray(rowCount) =  objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(0)&amp;&quot;-&quot;&amp;objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(1) &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp; objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(0) &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp;objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(1) &amp; &quot;,&quot; &amp; objMatches.Item(0).SubMatches(2)
                        End If
                End If
        Loop
End Sub</data>
                        </contents>
                        <filename>
                            <data>ListenCount.vbs</data>
                        </filename>
                    </script>
                </toolkit>
            </plugin>
        </sampler>

        <sampler name="WS">
            <plugin>
                <win-services></win-services>
            </plugin>
            <dataviews>
                <dataview name="WS">
                    <additions>
                        <var-headlines>
                            <data>
                                <headline>
                                    <data>CountRunning</data>
                                </headline>
                            </data>
                        </var-headlines>
                        <var-columns>
                            <data>

                            </tableColumnLabels>

                            <time>false</time>
                            <xml>false</xml>
                        </pluginDebug>
                    </message-tracker>

        <samplerGroup name="Extractor">
            <!--
100 Continue
This means that the server has received the request headers, and that the client should proceed to send the request body (in the case of a request for which a body needs to be sent; for example, a POST request). If the request body is large, sending it to a server when a request has already been rejected based upon inappropriate headers is inefficient. To have a server check if the request could be accepted based on the request's headers alone, a client must send Expect: 100-continue as a header in its initial request and check if a 100 Continue status code is received in response before continuing (or receive 417 Expectation Failed and not continue).
101 Switching Protocols
This means the requester has asked the server to switch protocols and the server is acknowledging that it will do so.
102 Processing (WebDAV; RFC 2518)
As a WebDAV request may contain many sub-requests involving file operations, it may take a long time to complete the request. This code indicates that the server has received and is processing the request, but no response is available yet.[2] This prevents the client from timing out and assuming the request was lost.
2xx Success[edit]
This class of status codes indicates the action requested by the client was received, understood, accepted and processed successfully.

200 OK
Standard response for successful HTTP requests. The actual response will depend on the request method used. In a GET request, the response will contain an entity corresponding to the requested resource. In a POST request the response will contain an entity describing or containing the result of the action.
201 Created
The request has been fulfilled and resulted in a new resource being created.
202 Accepted
The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed. The request might or might not eventually be acted upon, as it might be disallowed when processing actually takes place.
203 Non-Authoritative Information (since HTTP/1.1)
The server successfully processed the request, but is returning information that may be from another source.
204 No Content
The server successfully processed the request, but is not returning any content. Usually used as a response to a successful delete request.
205 Reset Content
The server successfully processed the request, but is not returning any content. Unlike a 204 response, this response requires that the requester reset the document view.
206 Partial Content
The server is delivering only part of the resource (byte serving) due to a range header sent by the client. The range header is used by tools like wget to enable resuming of interrupted downloads, or split a download into multiple simultaneous streams.
207 Multi-Status (WebDAV; RFC 4918)
The message body that follows is an XML message and can contain a number of separate response codes, depending on how many sub-requests were made.[3]
208 Already Reported (WebDAV; RFC 5842)
The members of a DAV binding have already been enumerated in a previous reply to this request, and are not being included again.
226 IM Used (RFC 3229)
The server has fulfilled a request for the resource, and the response is a representation of the result of one or more instance-manipulations applied to the current instance.[4]
3xx Redirection[edit]
This class of status code indicates the client must take additional action to complete the request. Many of these status codes are used in URL redirection.

A user agent may carry out the additional action with no user interaction only if the method used in the second request is GET or HEAD. A user agent should not automatically redirect a request more than five times, since such redirections usually indicate an infinite loop.

300 Multiple Choices
Indicates multiple options for the resource that the client may follow. It, for instance, could be used to present different format options for video, list files with different extensions, or word sense disambiguation.
301 Moved Permanently
This and all future requests should be directed to the given URI.
302 Found
This is an example of industry practice contradicting the standard. The HTTP/1.0 specification (RFC 1945) required the client to perform a temporary redirect (the original describing phrase was "Moved Temporarily"),[5] but popular browsers implemented 302 with the functionality of a 303 See Other. Therefore, HTTP/1.1 added status codes 303 and 307 to distinguish between the two behaviours.[6] However, some Web applications and frameworks use the 302 status code as if it were the 303.[7]
303 See Other (since HTTP/1.1)
The response to the request can be found under another URI using a GET method. When received in response to a POST (or PUT/DELETE), it should be assumed that the server has received the data and the redirect should be issued with a separate GET message.
304 Not Modified
Indicates that the resource has not been modified since the version specified by the request headers If-Modified-Since or If-None-Match. This means that there is no need to retransmit the resource, since the client still has a previously-downloaded copy.
305 Use Proxy (since HTTP/1.1)
The requested resource is only available through a proxy, whose address is provided in the response. Many HTTP clients (such as Mozilla[8] and Internet Explorer) do not correctly handle responses with this status code, primarily for security reasons.[9]
306 Switch Proxy
No longer used. Originally meant "Subsequent requests should use the specified proxy."[10]
307 Temporary Redirect (since HTTP/1.1)
In this case, the request should be repeated with another URI; however, future requests should still use the original URI. In contrast to how 302 was historically implemented, the request method is not allowed to be changed when reissuing the original request. For instance, a POST request should be repeated using another POST request.[11]
308 Permanent Redirect (Experimental RFC; RFC 7238)
The request, and all future requests should be repeated using another URI. 307 and 308 (as proposed) parallel the behaviours of 302 and 301, but do not allow the HTTP method to change. So, for example, submitting a form to a permanently redirected resource may continue smoothly.[12]
4xx Client Error[edit]

404 error on Polish Wikipedia
The 4xx class of status code is intended for cases in which the client seems to have errored. Except when responding to a HEAD request, the server should include an entity containing an explanation of the error situation, and whether it is a temporary or permanent condition. These status codes are applicable to any request method. User agents should display any included entity to the user.

400 Bad Request
The request could not be understood by the server due to malformed syntax.
401 Unauthorized
Similar to 403 Forbidden, but specifically for use when authentication is required and has failed or has not yet been provided. The response must include a WWW-Authenticate header field containing a challenge applicable to the requested resource. See Basic access authentication and Digest access authentication.
402 Payment Required
Reserved for future use. The original intention was that this code might be used as part of some form of digital cash or micropayment scheme, but that has not happened, and this code is not usually used. YouTube uses this status if a particular IP address has made excessive requests, and requires the person to enter a CAPTCHA.[citation needed]
403 Forbidden
The request was a valid request, but the server is refusing to respond to it. Unlike a 401 Unauthorized response, authenticating will make no difference.
404 Not Found
The requested resource could not be found but may be available again in the future. Subsequent requests by the client are permissible.
405 Method Not Allowed
A request was made of a resource using a request method not supported by that resource; for example, using GET on a form which requires data to be presented via POST, or using PUT on a read-only resource.
406 Not Acceptable
The requested resource is only capable of generating content not acceptable according to the Accept headers sent in the request.
407 Proxy Authentication Required
The client must first authenticate itself with the proxy.
408 Request Timeout
The server timed out waiting for the request. According to HTTP specifications: "The client did not produce a request within the time that the server was prepared to wait. The client MAY repeat the request without modifications at any later time."
409 Conflict
Indicates that the request could not be processed because of conflict in the request, such as an edit conflict in the case of multiple updates.
410 Gone
Indicates that the resource requested is no longer available and will not be available again. This should be used when a resource has been intentionally removed and the resource should be purged. Upon receiving a 410 status code, the client should not request the resource again in the future. Clients such as search engines should remove the resource from their indices. [citation needed] Most use cases do not require clients and search engines to purge the resource, and a "404 Not Found" may be used instead.
411 Length Required
The request did not specify the length of its content, which is required by the requested resource.
412 Precondition Failed
The server does not meet one of the preconditions that the requester put on the request.
413 Request Entity Too Large
The request is larger than the server is willing or able to process.
414 Request-URI Too Long
The URI provided was too long for the server to process. Often the result of too much data being encoded as a query-string of a GET request, in which case it should be converted to a POST request.
415 Unsupported Media Type
The request entity has a media type which the server or resource does not support. For example, the client uploads an image as image/svg+xml, but the server requires that images use a different format.
416 Requested Range Not Satisfiable
The client has asked for a portion of the file (byte serving), but the server cannot supply that portion. For example, if the client asked for a part of the file that lies beyond the end of the file.
417 Expectation Failed
The server cannot meet the requirements of the Expect request-header field.
418 I'm a teapot (RFC 2324)
This code was defined in 1998 as one of the traditional IETF April Fools' jokes, in RFC 2324, Hyper Text Coffee Pot Control Protocol, and is not expected to be implemented by actual HTTP servers.
419 Authentication Timeout (not in RFC 2616)
Not a part of the HTTP standard, 419 Authentication Timeout denotes that previously valid authentication has expired. It is used as an alternative to 401 Unauthorized in order to differentiate from otherwise authenticated clients being denied access to specific server resources.[citation needed]
420 Method Failure (Spring Framework)
Not part of the HTTP standard, but defined by Spring in the HttpStatus class to be used when a method failed. This status code is deprecated by Spring.
420 Enhance Your Calm (Twitter)
Not part of the HTTP standard, but returned by version 1 of the Twitter Search and Trends API when the client is being rate limited.[13] Other services may wish to implement the 429 Too Many Requests response code instead.
422 Unprocessable Entity (WebDAV; RFC 4918)
The request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to semantic errors.[3]
423 Locked (WebDAV; RFC 4918)
The resource that is being accessed is locked.[3]
424 Failed Dependency (WebDAV; RFC 4918)
The request failed due to failure of a previous request (e.g., a PROPPATCH).[3]
426 Upgrade Required
The client should switch to a different protocol such as TLS/1.0.
428 Precondition Required (RFC 6585)
The origin server requires the request to be conditional. Intended to prevent "the 'lost update' problem, where a client GETs a resource's state, modifies it, and PUTs it back to the server, when meanwhile a third party has modified the state on the server, leading to a conflict."[14]
429 Too Many Requests (RFC 6585)
The user has sent too many requests in a given amount of time. Intended for use with rate limiting schemes.[14]
431 Request Header Fields Too Large (RFC 6585)
The server is unwilling to process the request because either an individual header field, or all the header fields collectively, are too large.[14]
440 Login Timeout (Microsoft)
A Microsoft extension. Indicates that your session has expired.[15]
444 No Response (Nginx)
Used in Nginx logs to indicate that the server has returned no information to the client and closed the connection (useful as a deterrent for malware).
449 Retry With (Microsoft)
A Microsoft extension. The request should be retried after performing the appropriate action.[16]
Often search-engines or custom applications will ignore required parameters. Where no default action is appropriate, the Aviongoo website sends a "HTTP/1.1 449 Retry with valid parameters: param1, param2, . . ." response. The applications may choose to learn, or not.
450 Blocked by Windows Parental Controls (Microsoft)
A Microsoft extension. This error is given when Windows Parental Controls are turned on and are blocking access to the given webpage.[17]
451 Unavailable For Legal Reasons (Internet draft)
Defined in the internet draft "A New HTTP Status Code for Legally-restricted Resources".[18] Intended to be used when resource access is denied for legal reasons, e.g. censorship or government-mandated blocked access. A reference to the 1953 dystopian novel Fahrenheit 451, where books are outlawed.[19]
451 Redirect (Microsoft)
Used in Exchange ActiveSync if there either is a more efficient server to use or the server cannot access the users' mailbox.[20]
The client is supposed to re-run the HTTP Autodiscovery protocol to find a better suited server.[21]
494 Request Header Too Large (Nginx)
Nginx internal code similar to 431 but it was introduced earlier in version 0.9.4 (on January 21, 2011).[22][original research?]
495 Cert Error (Nginx)
Nginx internal code used when SSL client certificate error occurred to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection.
496 No Cert (Nginx)
Nginx internal code used when client didn't provide certificate to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection.
497 HTTP to HTTPS (Nginx)
Nginx internal code used for the plain HTTP requests that are sent to HTTPS port to distinguish it from 4XX in a log and an error page redirection.
498 Token expired/invalid (Esri)
Returned by ArcGIS for Server. A code of 498 indicates an expired or otherwise invalid token.[23]
499 Client Closed Request (Nginx)
Used in Nginx logs to indicate when the connection has been closed by client while the server is still processing its request, making server unable to send a status code back.[24]
499 Token required (Esri)
Returned by ArcGIS for Server. A code of 499 indicates that a token is required (if no token was submitted).[23]
5xx Server Error[edit]
The server failed to fulfill an apparently valid request.

Response status codes beginning with the digit "5" indicate cases in which the server is aware that it has encountered an error or is otherwise incapable of performing the request. Except when responding to a HEAD request, the server should include an entity containing an explanation of the error situation, and indicate whether it is a temporary or permanent condition. Likewise, user agents should display any included entity to the user. These response codes are applicable to any request method.

500 Internal Server Error
A generic error message, given when an unexpected condition was encountered and no more specific message is suitable.
501 Not Implemented
The server either does not recognize the request method, or it lacks the ability to fulfil the request. Usually this implies future availability (e.g., a new feature of a web-service API).
502 Bad Gateway
The server was acting as a gateway or proxy and received an invalid response from the upstream server.
503 Service Unavailable
The server is currently unavailable (because it is overloaded or down for maintenance). Generally, this is a temporary state.
504 Gateway Timeout
The server was acting as a gateway or proxy and did not receive a timely response from the upstream server.
505 HTTP Version Not Supported
The server does not support the HTTP protocol version used in the request.
506 Variant Also Negotiates (RFC 2295)
Transparent content negotiation for the request results in a circular reference.[25]
507 Insufficient Storage (WebDAV; RFC 4918)
The server is unable to store the representation needed to complete the request.[3]
508 Loop Detected (WebDAV; RFC 5842)
The server detected an infinite loop while processing the request (sent in lieu of 208 Already Reported).
509 Bandwidth Limit Exceeded (Apache bw/limited extension)[26]
This status code is not specified in any RFCs. Its use is unknown.
510 Not Extended (RFC 2774)
Further extensions to the request are required for the server to fulfil it.[27]
511 Network Authentication Required (RFC 6585)
The client needs to authenticate to gain network access. Intended for use by intercepting proxies used to control access to the network (e.g., "captive portals" used to require agreement to Terms of Service before granting full Internet access via a Wi-Fi hotspot).[14]
520 Origin Error (CloudFlare)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by CloudFlare's reverse proxies to signal an "unknown connection issue between CloudFlare and the origin web server" to a client in front of the proxy.
521 Web server is down (CloudFlare)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by CloudFlare's reverse proxies to indicate that the origin webserver refused the connection.[28]
522 Connection timed out (CloudFlare)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by CloudFlare's reverse proxies to signal that a server connection timed out.[29]
523 Proxy Declined Request (CloudFlare)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by CloudFlare's reverse proxies to signal a resource that has been blocked by the administrator of the website or proxy itself.
524 A timeout occurred (CloudFlare)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by CloudFlare's reverse proxies to signal a network read timeout behind the proxy to a client in front of the proxy.
598 Network read timeout error (Unknown)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by Microsoft HTTP proxies to signal a network read timeout behind the proxy to a client in front of the proxy.[citation needed]
599 Network connect timeout error (Unknown)
This status code is not specified in any RFCs, but is used by Microsoft HTTP proxies to signal a network connect timeout behind the proxy to a client in front of the proxy.-->

                                                                                </xpath>
                                                                            </value>
                                                                        </cell>
                                                                    </cells>
                                                                </row>
                                                            </rows>
                                                        </xpath>
                                                    </method>
                                                </html>
                                            </format>
                                        </custom>
                                    </template>

        <samplerGroup name="Filecounters">
            <sampler name="Windows filecounter_part1">
                <!--This sampler has no sampling interval and is purely to deploy the bat script.
It is used by the listfilecount.bat sampler.
-->
                <sampleInterval>
                    <data>0</data>
                </sampleInterval>
                <sampleOnStartup>false</sampleOnStartup>
                <plugin>
                    <toolkit>
                        <samplerScript>
                            <data>FileCountNoHeading</data>
                        </samplerScript>
                        <script>
                            <contents>
                                <data>@echo off
dir /B %1 | find /v /c &quot;?&quot; &gt; tempfile.txt
set /P count=&lt;tempfile.txt
call :dequote %1
echo %ret%, %count%


:dequote
setlocal
set thestring=%~1
endlocal&amp;set ret=%thestring%
goto :eof
</data>
                            </contents>
                            <filename>
                                <data>FileCountNoHeading.bat</data>
                            </filename>
                        </script>
                    </toolkit>
                </plugin>
            </sampler>
            <sampler name="Windows filecounter_part2">
                <!--Usage is: 
listfilecount path [/s]

The /s option adds subdirectory counts, but can slow it down significantly
depending on the path that's passed in.

N.B.  Will not include hidden files in the count.-->
                <sampleInterval>
                    <data>0</data>
                </sampleInterval>
                <sampleOnStartup>true</sampleOnStartup>
                <plugin>
                    <toolkit>
                        <samplerScript>
                            <data>listfilecount.bat C:\DB_FEB10 /s</data>
                        </samplerScript>
                        <script>
                            <contents>
                                <data>@echo off
if (%1) == () goto USAGE

echo Folder, File Count
if (%2) == (/s) goto RECURSIVE

dir /B %1 | find /v /c &quot;?&quot; &gt; tempfile.txt
set /P count=&lt;tempfile.txt
echo %1, %count%
goto END

:RECURSIVE

dir /X /A:D /B %1 %2 &gt; list.txt
FOR /F &quot;delims=?&quot; %%A IN (list.txt) DO call filecountnoheading.bat &quot;%%A&quot;
goto END

:USAGE
echo usage: listfilecount path [/s]
:END
</data>
                            </contents>
                            <filename>
                                <data>ListFileCount.bat</data>
                            </filename>
                        </script>
                    </toolkit>
                </plugin>
            </sampler>
        </samplerGroup>

                <plugin>
                    <Gateway-sql>
                        <tables>
                            <dataview>
                                <tableName>
                                    <data>TrialTypes</data>
                                </tableName>
                                <xpath>/geneos/gateway[(@name=&quot;TheOneAndOnlyGW2_RJB  port 9886&quot;)]/directory/probe[(@name=&quot;RJBVM_32&quot;)]/managedEntity[(@name=&quot;SQLlite&quot;)]/sampler[(@name=&quot;select the last active toolkit&quot;)][(@type=&quot;&quot;)]/dataview[(@name=&quot;select the last active toolkit&quot;)]</xpath>
                            </dataview>
                        </tables>
                        <views>
                            <view>
                                <name>
                                    <data>test</data>
                                </name>
                                <sql>
                                    <data>SELECT t1.*
FROM TrialTypes t1
LEFT OUTER JOIN TrialTypes t2 ON t1.name = t2.name 
AND (t1.timestamp &lt; t2.timestamp OR t1.timestamp = t2.timestamp AND t1.rowid &lt; t2.rowid )
WHERE t2.name IS NULL and t1.status != &apos;inactive&apos;</data>
                                </sql>
                            </view>
                            <view>
                                <name>
                                    <data>test2</data>
                                </name>
                                <sql>
                                    <data>select name, status,   max(timestamp) as timestamp
from TrialTypes 
where status = &apos;active&apos; 
group by name, status</data>
                                </sql>
                            </view>
                        </views>
                    </Gateway-sql>
                </plugin>

                                    <xpaths>
                                        <xpath>/geneos/gateway[(@name=&quot;QA EMEA&quot;)]/directory/probe[(@name=&quot;gbvmapmdsp001&quot;)]/managedEntity[(@name=&quot;gbvmapmdsp001&quot;)]/sampler/dataview[(@name=&quot;TOF&quot;)]/rows/row/cell[(@column=&quot;TCID&quot;)]</xpath>
                                    </xpaths>
                                    <columns>
                                        <column>
                                            <name>
                                                <data>ID</data>
                                            </name>

                                            <type>TEXT</type>
                                        </column>

                                            <name>
                                                <data>TCID</data>
                                            </name>

                                            <name>
                                                <data>TOF Service</data>

                                        </column>

                                            <name>
                                                <data>TOF LBN</data>

                                        </column>

                                            <name>

                            </tables>
                            <views>
                                <view>
                                    <name>
                                        <data>CP Summary</data>
                                    </name>
                                    <sql>
                                        <data>select * from CP</data>
                                    </sql>
                                    <showRowID>true</showRowID>
                                </view>
                                <view>
                                    <name>
                                        <data>DTFE Summary</data>
                                    </name>
                                    <sql>
                                        <data>select * from DTFE</data>
                                    </sql>
                                    <showRowID>true</showRowID>
                                </view>
                                <view>
                                    <name>
                                        <data>Ticket Printer Summary</data>
                                    </name>
                                    <sql>
                                        <data>select * from TP</data>
                                    </sql>
                                    <showRowID>true</showRowID>
                                </view>
                                <view>
                                    <name>
                                        <data>TOF Summary</data>
                                    </name>
                                    <sql>
                                        <data>select * from TOF</data>
                                    </sql>
                                    <showRowID>true</showRowID>
                                </view>
                                <view>
                                    <name>
                                        <data>Combined Summary</data>
                                    </name>
                                    <sql>
                                        <data>SELECT
  TOF.ID,
  TOF.&quot;TOF Service&quot;,
  TOF.&quot;TOF LBN&quot;,
  TOF.&quot;TOF Port&quot;,
  TOF.&quot;TOF Client Connection&quot;,
  DTFE.&quot;DTFE Service&quot;,
  DTFE.&quot;DTFE LBN&quot;,
  TP.&quot;TP Service&quot;,
  TP.&quot;TP LBN&quot;,
  CP.&quot;Conv Prt Service&quot;,
  CP.&quot;Conv Prt LBN&quot;
FROM TOF
LEFT JOIN DTFE 
ON TOF.TCID=DTFE.TCID
LEFT JOIN TP
ON TOF.TCID=TP.TCID
LEFT JOIN CP
ON TOF.TCID=CP.TCID</data>
                                    </sql>
                                </view>
                            </views>
                        </Gateway-sql>

        <samplerGroup disabled="true" name="Missing Execs Original">
            <samplerGroup name="Missing Executions">
                <sampler name="INPUT">
                    <sampleInterval>
                        <data>10</data>
                    </sampleInterval>
                    <plugin>
                        <message-tracker>
                            <adapters>
                                <adapter name="InputLog">
                                    <checkpoint>
                                        <data>INPUT</data>
                                    </checkpoint>
                                    <source>
                                        <file>
                                            <filename>
                                                <data>/apps/efg-ax2/FSA65_ETP02/logs/Daily</data>
                                            </filename>
                                        </file>
                                    </source>
                                    <formatType>
                                        <data>
                                            <regex>
                                                <tags>
                                                    <tag name="EXCH">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>10005=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="EXCH_TRD_CODE">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>10006=.+EXCH_TRD_CODE=(.+?)\|</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG55">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>55=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG32">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>32=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG31">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>31=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG207">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>207=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG54">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>54=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG15">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>15=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="CLIENTID">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>10006=CLIENT=(.+?)\|</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                    <tag name="TAG8001">
                                                        <data>
                                                            <regex>8001=(.+?)\001</regex>
                                                        </data>
                                                    </tag>
                                                </tags>
                                            </regex>
                                            <timestamp>
                                                <regexPattern>
                                                    <data>
                                                        <regex>(^.{23}) </regex>
                                                    </data>
                                                </regexPattern>
                                                <format>
                                                    <data>%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S,%Of</data>
                                                </format>
                                            </timestamp>
                                        </data>
                                    </formatType>
                                    <filters>
                                        <message>
                                            <match>in.ETP_GBOI.*8056=(DMAOMA|NYOMAR).*EXCH_TRD_CODE</match>
                                            <invert>false</invert>
                                        </message>

                <sampler name="CARE 21_3">
                    <!--Recording XML commented out as unable to establish a connection to the mysql database.

Uncomment the XML when bug is fixed

Real-time tracking (RTT) debug:
===============================

>>discardQueue
Outputs info when a message is removed (and discarded) rather than lost.
I feel this setting is slightly misnamed and sounds worse than it really is...
This condition will occur if a parent checkpoint P tells child checkpoint C to expect a message, and C later replies that this message has been seen. At this point P discards the message. If the message is not discarded, it will eventually be marked as lost, and appear in the lost messages view.
In non-unique orders mode you may also see output on C, if P has said to expect several messages with the same order ID. Because we expect to see Order/Ack/Order/Ack in this mode, only the last Order message is kept and the rest discarded. Doing this causes the parent to eventually mark those discarded orders as lost.

>>average
As far as I can see, this does nothing. I will remove it next time I change the MessageTracker config schema.

>>interprobeComms
Displays debug for the connection state, when using remote checkpoints and/or adapters.

>>interprobeCommsDetails
Displays debug on comms events when using remote checkpoints and/or adapters. These include heartbeats, state changes and when data is received.

>>measured
Displays debug output when a new latency value has been found (when an order is acknowledged). Details include the start and end-time, and calculated latency (in seconds I think).

>>queue
Displays debug info when a message is moved between queues on a checkpoint. These are actually shown by describing the event which has occurred. E.g. "MESSAGE ARRIVAL WAITED" means that a message has been received, and is now in a queue waiting for a child checkpoint to respond to it. "MESSAGE FORWARDED" would typically be displayed almost directly after this, and means that the parent checkpoint is informing the children to look for this message.

>>queueDetails
Additional debug details for queues. Seems to output info when queues are emptied, when messages are moved to the "lost" queue.

>>queueMonitor
Enables additional dataviews, displaying the internal message queues for each checkpoint.

>>queueSize
Does nothing, but there is an additional setting "statResize" which outputs messages when the statistics buffers are increased in size (for the latency average and std.dev calculations). I will change this next time I alter the setup.


Adapter debug:
==============

>>adapter-msg
Outputs debug information for data received via XML-RPC, for both external adapters and client adapters.


Plug-in debug:
==============

>>adapter-view
Adds an "adapter" field to the admin view. This field can be used to see which adapters are sharing the same data source (file reader).

>>catchup
Displays debug details related to the "catchup adapter" functionality, which would rescan the early parts of a file if the plug-in was started in the middle of the day. This feature has currently been disabled due to the changes made to database logging (in the version that introduced the v2 database schema).

>>db-connections
Displays debug messages about the plug-in database connection status.

>>db-insert
Displays debug messages when an insert was performed, when using v1 schema.

>>db-statment-log
Displays debug messages about each SQL statement being executed.

>>db-process
Not sure... this was likely a v1 schema debug message of some kind.

>>exec
Prints out a message each time an XML-RPC method call is made, with the name of the method being executed.

>>flow
Displays messages when the plug-in performs a sample.
-->
